      • doBaseChecks

        protected void doBaseChecks(OperationType operationType,
                            Operand[] operands,
                            boolean doNullCheck,
                            boolean doSupportedTypesCheck)
        This method is used to do some base checks that must be done before most operations.

        This includes checks for number of operands(mandatory) and supportedTypeCheck(optional) and null checks for operation type, operands (mandatory) and operand values (optional).

        Parameters:
        operationType - the operation type to check for
        operands - the operands of the operation
        doNullCheck - Defines if null checks for operand values should be done
        doSupportedTypesCheck - Defines if operand types should be checked for conformity with operation
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if a constraint is violated
